iving region (<b>18</b><i>a</i>-<b>18</b><i>f</i>) for the wiper arm adapter (<b>12</b><i>a</i>-<b>12</b><i>f</i>) in a wiping direction (<b>20</b><i>a</i>-<b>20</b>f), and a rotational joint unit (<b>22</b><i>a</i>-<b>22</b><i>f</i>) of the wiper blade adapter (<b>10</b><i>a</i>-<b>10</b><i>f</i>) is arranged inside the receiving region (<b>18</b><i>a</i>-<b>18</b><i>f</i>), said unit bearing the wiper arm adapter (<b>12</b><i>a</i>-<b>12</b><i>f</i>) in a mounted state.</p></abstract></us-patent-application>